The UV-protection factors (UPF) of films were measured by the AATCC 183–2010 using a UV–vis spectrophotometer, where Tλ is the light transmittance of TCC/DAC-TH films. The air was used as the control reference. UPF was measured from the transmission spectra of the films in the range of 290–400 nm using the following equation34:UPF=∑290400E(λ)·S(λ)∑290400E(λ)·S(λ)·T(λ)·Δ(λ)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
