				\begin{document}$$UPF = \frac{{\sum\nolimits_{290}^{400} {E(\lambda ) \cdot S(\lambda )} }}{{\sum\nolimits_{290}^{400} {E(\lambda ) \cdot S(\lambda )} \cdot T(\lambda ) \cdot \Delta (\lambda )}}$$\end{document}where E(λ) is the relative erythemal spectral effectiveness, S(λ) is the solar spectral irradiance in Wm−2 nm−1. The values were provided by the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration database (NOAA)), T(λ) is the spectral transfer of the data taken from UV spectrophotometric tests, and Δ(λ) is the variation among observable wavelengths.
